    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "3a94a0f3716fd09c",
      "text": "Rituals can be seen as a way of [[limit]]ing reflexive communication by fixing the elements of the communication process in a rigid and unchanging manner. In rituals, words are treated as objects, the present moment is considered unchangeable, and the use of symbols is minimized to minimize risk. This rigidity eliminates the need to question the process, making rituals similar to everyday facts that are accepted without questioning."
    }
