        "text": "One can understand rituals from the point of view of coupling all approaches to reflexive communication . Communication is stiffened as a fixed process, and its rigidity itself takes the place of asking why this is so . The elements of the process and their order are fixed irrevocably, words are treated like things, the present counts and is not correctable either with regard to the future or on the basis of past experiences accrued in each case. The risk of using symbols is kept as low as possible. Rituals are comparable to the unquestioning self-evident facts of everyday life, which also eliminate reflexivity."
